      <td colspan="2" valign="top" style="border-bottom: 1px solid #CCCCCC;padding:0px 14px 18px 14px;">
      	<h1 style="margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:18px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;"><a id="letter"></a>Letter from Lynda</h1>
		<div style="float: left; margin: 4px 12px 12px 0;">
		<img src="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/newsletter/apr10/lynda.jpg" alt="Lynda Weinman" border="0" />
		<p style="margin:4px 0;text-align:center;font-size:10px;font-style:italic;color:#666;">Photo: Douglas Kirkland 2010</p>
		</div>
<p>Dear Members and Newsletter Subscribers,</p>

<p>At the halfway mark through the year, we&rsquo;ve released over 120 new courses&mdash;a new record! This is made possible through you, our growing membership, who via your support make it possible for us to keep our prices the same, but grow the value and volume of our offering year after year. </p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;">New Creative Inspirations: <em>Natalie Fobes, Photographer</em></h2>

<p><a href="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/trailers/trailer62349.html?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_LL&utm_campaign=Newsletters" alias="Natalie Fobes, Photographer"><img src="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/newsletter/july10/july2010newsletter_natalie.jpg" alt="" border="0" /></a></p>

<p>I had the pleasure of meeting the featured artist in our latest Creative Inspirations documentary, photographer Natalie Forbes, when I was in Seattle a few months ago. Among other accomplishments, Natalie was the chief photographer covering the Exxon Valdez oil spill for <cite>National Geographic</cite>, currently teaches at a local college, continues with portrait and wedding photography, and gets to be home for the kid&rsquo;s soccer games. Sound like a dream career? She has great wisdom and artistry to share. <a href="http://www.lynda.com/home/DisplayCourse.aspx?lpk2=62349?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_LL&utm_campaign=Newsletters" style="color: #000000;text-decoration: underline;">Be sure to check it out!</a></p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;">New courses on Lightroom 3</h2>

<p>Adobe released a new version of Lightroom in June, and we&rsquo;ve published two new courses created by renowned photographer, and <a style="color: #000000;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> author Chris Orwig.</p>

<p><a href="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/trailers/trailer59973.html?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_LL&utm_campaign=Newsletters" alias="Photoshop Lightroom 3 New Features" style="float: left;margin: 0px 12px 5px 0px;"><img style="margin:5px 0px 0px 0px;" src="http://files2.lynda.com/files/images/courses/59973_Trailer.jpg" border="0" alt=""/></a>In <a href="http://www.lynda.com/home/DisplayCourse.aspx?lpk2=59973&utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_LL&utm_campaign=Newsletters" style="text-decoration: underline;color: #000000;font-style: italic;">Photoshop Lightroom 3 New Features</a>, Chris explores the enhancements that Adobe Photoshop Lightroom 3 brings to each phase of the photographic workflowâ€”from importing and editing, to exporting and publishing. This course details Lightroom 3&rsquo;s new importing and asset-management features and its significant improvements in the Develop module, including enhanced sharpening and noise reduction. Chris also shows how Lightroom 3 broadens output options, and shares workflow tips and advice for upgrading Lightroom 2 catalogs and working with images processed in earlier Lightroom versions.</p>

<p><a href="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/trailers/trailer59972.html?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_LL&utm_campaign=Newsletters" alias="Photoshop Lightroom 3 Essential Training" style="float: left;margin: 0px 12px 5px 0px;"><img style="margin:5px 0px 0px 0px;" src="http://files2.lynda.com/files/images/courses/59972_Trailer.jpg" border="0" alt=""/></a> Then, in <a href="http://www.lynda.com/home/DisplayCourse.aspx?lpk2=59972&utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_LL&utm_campaign=Newsletters" style="text-decoration: underline;color: #000000;font-style: italic;">Photoshop Lightroom 3 Essential Training</a>, Chris covers indispensable techniques such as importing, processing, and organizing images in the Library, correcting and adjusting images in the Develop module, and creating slideshows, web galleries, and print picture packages. In addition to exploring all of Lightroom 3&rsquo;s capabilities, this course is rich with creative tips and expert advice on photographic workflow.</p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;">Jan Kabili gets Scobalized</h2>

<p><a href="http://blog.lynda.com/2010/06/11/lynda-com-author-jan-kabili-demos-photoshop-cs5-features-for-building-43?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_blog_061110_jkabili&utm_campaign=Newsletters" style="text-decoration: underline;color: #000000;">Watch lynda.com author Jan Kabili</a> show off the new features of Photoshop CS5 to Robert Scoble on his prolific Building 43 blog site. Caution: you will learn new tips and techniques!</p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;"><a style="color: #7C2001;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> iPhone App update</h2>

<p><a style="color: #000000;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> iPhone App version 1.1.1 was released on June 20th, and here&rsquo;s what&rsquo;s new:</p>
<p>&bull; It&rsquo;s been tested and bugs have been fixed for optimal iPhone OS4 support<br />&bull; Minor general bug fixes</p>

<p>If you have a previous version of the <a style="color: #000000;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> iPhone App installed, open the App Store app on your iPhone or iPod Touch, and click on the <strong>Updates</strong> icon. It should be listed as an available update in the App Store.</p>

<p>If you haven&rsquo;t installed the <a style="color: #000000;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> iPhone App yet, head over to <a href="http://www.lynda.com/lynda_iphone.aspx?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_iPhoneAppUpdate&utm_campaign=Newsletters" style="text-decoration: underline;color: #000000;">our lynda.com iPhone App page</a> and click on the Download from the App Store button. It will take you directly to the <a style="color: #000000;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> iPhone App page in iTunes.</p> 

<p>Even though the iPhone app works on the iPad, the experience is better if you use Safari. We are in development of a universal app for both iPhone and iPad which will be released by end of year. As well, we are working hard on a <a style="color: #000000;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> mobile site that will be compatible with all smart phones.</p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;"><a style="color: #7C2001;text-decoration: none;">lynda.com</a> now accepts PayPal</h2>

<p>We&rsquo;ve got PayPal working on the registration side of the site, but in this phase, only new membership accounts can pay with PayPal. Don&rsquo;t worry though, we&rsquo;re working on setting up our system to allow current members to convert your payment method as an option, as you&rsquo;ve requested.</p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;">How do you use bookmarks?</h2>

<p>We introduced our new Bookmarks feature in the Online Training Library&reg; back in January, and we&rsquo;re curious how you&rsquo;ve been using them. How often do you use them to mark and tag courses, chapters, individual video tutorials, and to mark specific points in a video in order to find a topic or technique again later? Do you add details to your bookmarks by clicking on the arrow next to the bookmark icon, or add tags to make it easier to sort your bookmarks? <a href="http://blog.lynda.com/2010/06/30/how-do-you-use-lynda-com-bookmarks?utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_blog_063010_bookmarks&utm_campaign=Newsletters" style="color: #000000;text-decoration: underline;">Stop by our blog and let us know</a>.</p>

<h2 style="clear: both; margin: 10px 0px 12px 0px;font-size:14px;color:#7C2001;font-family:'Trebuchet MS', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;clear: both;">More soon</h2>

<p>We have some exciting enhancements to the website coming around the corner. More to report next monthâ€”until then, Happy Learning! &mdash; Lynda</p>
