              <td valign="top" style="border-bottom: 0px solid #CCCCCC;padding:0px 14px 10px 5px;"><table style="margin:18px 0px;background-color:#E6E6E6;font-size:12px;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="293">
          <tr>
            <td colspan="2" valign="top"><a style="color: #000; text-decoration: underline;" id="hottip"></a><img src="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/newsletter/july10/hottipofthemonth.gif" alt="" height="76" width="293" /></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top" style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px;" width="275"><a style="color: #000; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.lynda.com/home/DisplayCourse.aspx?lpk2=62219&utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_hottip_thumb&utm_campaign=Newsletters" alias="Word 2010 Essential Training (hottip)"><img style="border: 0;" src="http://files2.lynda.com/files/lol_email/newsletter/july10/July2010HOTtip.jpg" alt="HOT Tip of the Month" /></a><p style="margin:4px 0;text-align:center;font-size:10px;font-style:italic;color:#666;">While tracking changes, inline changes with balloons lets you see your formatting in the margin, and the text you changed inline.</p>
			</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td colspan="2" valign="top" style="padding:10px; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"><p><strong>Tracking Changes and Showing Markup</strong><br />
			from <em>Word 2010 Essential Training</em><br />with Gini Courter</p>
			
			<p>Track Changes is a useful tool any time that you work collaboratively with others on a document. Whether you&rsquo;re reviewing a document for someone else, sending a document to others for review, or creating a markup document with inline changes for a public discussion, Track Changes makes it easy to follow changes and create a final, collaborative document. Each change made to the document is noted with the appropriate author&rsquo;s information, and in final review, changes can either be accepted or rejected.</p>
			
			<p>With your document open, turn on tracking by simply clicking the Track Changes button. As you edit your document, all of your changes are shown in balloons along the margin and a grey line along the edge of the changed text indicating which section of the document has changes made.</p>
			
			<p>If you prefer to see changes made inline instead of in balloons, choose <strong>Show Markup &gt; Balloons &gt; Show formatting inline</strong>. The same grey line marks the edge of changed copy, deleted text is marked with strikeout, and proposed new text is underlined. Changes in this view may be hard to see. You can get the best of both by selecting <strong>Balloon &gt; Show Only Comments and Formatting in Balloons</strong>. This is the best of both worlds&mdash;you can see your formatting in the margin and the text you changed inline.</p>
			
			<p>View sample movies for <cite><a style="color: #000; text-decoration: underline;" href="http://www.lynda.com/home/DisplayCourse.aspx?lpk2=62219&utm_source=LDCemail&utm_medium=email&utm_content=NL070710_hottip_text&utm_campaign=Newsletters" class="links">Word 2010 Essential Training</a>.</cite></p>
			</td>
          </tr>
       </table>
